      Under the Copyright Law of the People's Republic of China, the
      right of attribution (署名权) is a moral right (人身权) of the
      author that is protected in perpetuity and CANNOT be waived,
      transferred, or extinguished (著作权法 第二十二条). This condition
      survives the expiration of all economic rights.

  3.2 Integrity (著作权法 第十条第一款第四项 保护作品完整权)

      The Licensee shall not distort, mutilate, or alter the Work in
      a manner that is prejudicial to the author's honor or reputation.
      Derivative works shall clearly indicate the modifications made
      and shall not be represented as the original Work.

      Under the Copyright Law of the People's Republic of China, the
      right of integrity (保护作品完整权) is a moral right (人身权)
      protected in perpetuity and CANNOT be waived or transferred
      (著作权法 第二十二条).

  3.3 Modification (著作权法 第十条第一款第三项 修改权)

      The Licensee may create derivative works as permitted under
      Section 2(3), provided that the author's right of modification
      (修改权) is respected: any modifications shall be clearly
      identified, and the modified Work shall not be attributed to the
      original author as if it were the author's own expression.

      Under the Copyright Law of the People's Republic of China, the
      right of modification (修改权) is a moral right (人身权) protected
      in perpetuity and CANNOT be waived or transferred (著作权法
      第二十二条).

  3.4 No Endorsement

      The Licensee shall not use the name of the author or the
      Licensor to assert or imply endorsement of any derivative work
      without prior written consent.

