  4.2 Under P.R.C. Copyright Law (著作权法):

      (a) Moral Rights (人身权): The author's right of publication
          (发表权), right of attribution (署名权), right of
          modification (修改权), and right of integrity (保护作品
          完整权) are retained by the author in perpetuity and CANNOT
          be waived, transferred, or extinguished under any
          circumstances (著作权法 第二十二条). These rights are NOT
          licensed to the Licensee and remain exclusively with the
          author.

      (b) Economic Rights (财产权): The economic rights licensed under
          Section 2 include reproduction (复制权), distribution
          (发行权), adaptation (改编权), translation (翻译权),
          compilation (汇编权), and information network dissemination
          (信息网络传播权). The term of protection for economic rights
          is the life of the author plus fifty (50) years (著作权法
          第二十三条).

      (c) Notwithstanding the above, the moral rights of attribution
          (署名权), modification (修改权), and integrity (保护作品完整
          权) shall be honored worldwide, including in jurisdictions
          that do not formally recognize perpetual moral rights, as a
          contractual condition of this Agreement.

